LHS has become a hot topic of research in recent years. In the initial stage of heat storage, the same as the SHS, as the temperature of the heat storage material increases, the heat absorbed gradually increases, but the difference is that when the temperature reaches the phase transition point, the heat storage material continues to absorb heat without further increment of temperature during phase transition process. After the phase transition is complete, the temperature continues to increase as SHS. Therefore, the amount of heat stored could be expressed as:2Q=m·∫TinitialTmeltCp,sdT+m·ΔH+m·∫TmeltTfinalCp,ldT\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
